---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="What blog.oriz.in collects, what it doesn't, and your rights."
>
  <header class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-12 pb-6 border-b border-neutral-800">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-200">Blog</a> /
      <a href="/legal/" class="hover:text-neutral-200">Legal</a> / Privacy
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 prose prose-invert">
    <h2>Who runs this</h2>
    <p>
      blog.oriz.in and every <code>*.oriz.in</code> subdomain are operated by Chirag Singhal,
      based in Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India. Contact:
      <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and country.
        Cookieless. No personal identifiers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Authentication</strong> — if you sign in, Firebase Authentication stores
        your email, display name, and profile photo (if you sign in with Google/GitHub).
        We never see your password.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Site-specific data</strong> — when you save a bookmark or follow
        a series, it is stored in Firestore under your user ID and accessible
        only to you.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact form</strong> — submissions go through Web3Forms which
        forwards them to my email. Web3Forms keeps copies; see their privacy policy.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Comments</strong> — handled by Giscus, which stores your comment
        in a public GitHub Discussion.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Display ads</strong> — once approved, Google AdSense may set
        cookies to personalize ads. You can opt out via the consent banner or
        at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">adssettings.google.com</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No tracking across sessions for analytics (Cloudflare is anonymous).</li>
      <li>No selling of personal data to third parties.</li>
      <li>No newsletters unless you explicitly subscribe.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You can delete your account from the <a href="/account/">account page</a>;
      this removes your Firebase Auth record. To delete site-specific data
      (bookmarks, etc.), use the in-site delete tools or email me.
    </p>
    <p>
      Under India's DPDP Act 2023, you have the right to access, correct,
      and delete your personal data. Contact the
      <a href="/legal/grievance/">grievance officer</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      blog.oriz.in is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a child has
      provided data to us, contact the grievance officer for removal.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We will update this page when the practice changes, with the new date
      at the top. Material changes get a banner on the site.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
